# Compact Execution Quality

- Keep user-facing responses concise by default.
- Do full implementation work; do not skip validation, error handling, or tests.
- Prefer deterministic contracts across backend/frontend (shared field names and types).
- Use focused diffs and avoid unrelated refactors.
- When touching queues, enforce idempotent job IDs and retry policy.
- When touching external APIs, surface provenance/freshness in stored and returned data.
- Before claiming done, run relevant checks and report any remaining risk explicitly.
